I faced an issue with a a custom `TextWatcher` in Android 10. 

The issue was that our custom `TextWatcher` was keeping a reference to the `Editable` passed in as a parameter of `afterTextChanged`.

This reference was compared to the new `Editable` every time `afterTextChanged` is called.

Apparently, on Android 10, the `Editable` instance is always the same across `afterTextChanged` invocations.

This was not the case before Android 10, hence the issue and this question.

